JOHANNESBURG - South Africa's business confidence has jumped by the highest margin since the mid-1970s but it remains below the 50 point mark, which represents contraction. The Bureau for Economic Research has reported an increase of 11 points to 45 in the first quarter of this year. READ: Rand firms on Nene downgrade confidence This is a rare jump last seen in 1975. The bureau says if sustained, the first quarter rise could imply much-improved economic growth performance for the rest of the year. eNCA